16. d4( { Black plays on domination, now the knight on  d1  doesn't have squares to go to. However, the pawn advance weakens the  c4 -square. After }16...Rae8 17.Re1 Qd6 18.Re3 { with ideas like  b3  and  Bb2  or simply  Bf1 . White's material advantage is not contested at all as Black doesn't have any compensation. } )
