22. Rfd1{ White is a clear pawn up. Black's only compensation is the centralised knight, but that is a static compensation that White can try to neutralise by exchanging it or playing around it. White will play  Kf2  to centralise the king and then will seek an appropriate moment either to exchange the knight on  d4  or to advance the a-pawn. }
