9. Bg3{ Still aiming for a big centre with  e4 . }
9. f5{ Black still tries to stop  e4 . }
10. Nh3{ The  e4  push is a long-term idea, but in the meantime White can finish development with  e3 ,  Be2  ( d3 ,  c4 ) and  O-O . }
10. O-O
11. e3{ White has a very pleasant position. The development is smooth, the bishop will move from  f1  to  e2 ,  d3  or  c4 , castling will follow and the rook will come to  c1  to exert pressure on the pawn on  c7 . }
