8. Bf5{ An active spot for the bishop. }
9. Nd2{ White controls the important  e4 -square and prepares for a kingside expansion. Another idea of the move is to support the undermining with  b3  on the queenside. }
9. Be7( { In case of }9...Bd6 { White can either exchange on  d6  and continue with  b3 , or he can pin the knight on  f6  with }10.Bg5 Be7 11.Be2 { and follow up with  O-O ,  Bf3  and  b3 . } )
