17. f3{ Taking control of the  e4 -square and preparing  Kf2  and  g4 . The position is complicated with chances for both sides. Black will try to place the knights on solid outposts ( c4  is one, while the  g5 -square can be another one, effectively stopping White's idea to open the g-file with  g5 ) while White will use the bishops to support the advance of the pawn mass on the kingside, ideally by pushing  g5 . }
