18. Kf2{ Removing the king from the e-file and defending the  e3 -pawn so that the queen can move from  e2 . White's main plan is  Rag1 ,  g4 - g5 , with the queen joining the attack from  c2 , or alternatively with  Bc2  and  Qd3 . Black should prevent this by playing ... Nh7 - g5 . A sample line leading to extremely sharp play is }
18. b5
