10. b5
11. Bb3{ Still keeping an eye on the  d5 -square. }
11. Bb7( { In case of }11...b4 12.Na4 { (the move }12.d5!? { leads to very interesting complications) the  c5 -square becomes a landing destination for the knight after }{   }12...Bb7 13.Nc5 { . } )
12. Bf4( { White finished development and is ready to play in the centre. From  f4  the bishop is active on the  h2 - b8  diagonal and can come to  e5 , to bolster the IQP. The move }12.Bg5 { is the main theoretical move and a major alternative. } )
12. b4( { Black fights for control of the  d5 -square. In case of }12...Nbd7?! 13.d5! { is very strong. } )
13. Na4( { Again the sharp }13.d5!? { is possible, leading to complications where White tries to use Black's vulnerability on the d-file. The knight move is more positional, aiming for the  c5 -square. } )
