12. Bf8
13. Qd2{ Connecting the rooks. }
13. h6{ A useful move for Black, similar to White's  11.h3 . }
14. Rad1{ White is fully developed. In view of Black's good defences on the kingside his plan is to advance on the queenside with  c4  and in the centre with  d5 . If the centre is closed as Black reacts with ... c5  to White's  d5 , then a typical queenside expansion with  b4  will follow. A useful manoeuvre in such a closed position is the bishop transfer  Bc2 - a4 , activating the light-squared bishop. An exchange of the light-squared bishops would be in White's favour as his is the more limited one (his pawns in the centre are all on light squares), plus the exchange of Black's light-squared bishop would weaken the  f5 -square, so an attack with  Nf5  and  g4  becomes a possibility. }
