3. Bd3( { This developing move has two ideas: the first is to defend the pawn on  e4  and the second one is to keep the  c3 -square free so that White can strengthen the centre with  c3  and blunt Black's fianchettoed bishop on  g7 . Now Black has two main options: the Philidor players would likely play }3...e5 { , while the Pirc players would choose }3...g6 { . } )
