15. Rxa8
16. dxe5{ White can also take with a knight, as the plan is to take twice on  e5 . }
16. Nxe5
17. Nxe5( { White can also exchange on  e4 , }17.Bxe4 fxe4 18.Nxe5 Qxe5 19.Qd2 { when the main ideas are to push  b4  and win the  d4 -square in case Black removes the  c5 -pawn and to attack the pawn on  d5  by  Rd1  and  Nf4 . } )
17. Qxe5
18. Qc2{ White defends the pawn on  c3  and the idea of  Qb2  and  Ra1  is again possible. White has the more compact position, while Black's is over-extended. The undermining move  b4  is one idea for White, when in case of ... cxb4  or ... c4  White would obtain control of the  d4 -square. If Black keeps the pawn on  c5  then an exchange on  c5  would open the b-file that White can use to penetrate Black's position. Another idea, mentioned in the previous note, is the capture on  e4  followed by  Nf4  and  Rd1 , putting pressure on the  d5 -pawn. }
