27. b6{ Black covers the  c5 -square, so Botvinnik sends the knight to  d3  and  e5 . }
28. Nb2
28. a5
29. Nd3
29. f6{ Black managed to patch up the holes on  c5  and  e5 . However, his position remains passive and White continues to put pressure. }
30. h4{ White wants to push  g5  and exchange the  f6 -pawn, thus gaining access to the  e5 -square. }
