12. Kh1{ But with the bishop on  d6  Botvinnik masterfully changes the direction - he starts to prepare the central advance with  f3  and  e4 , particularly effective when the bishop is on  d6 , for two reasons: first, with the d-file blocked Black doesn't have pressure on the  d4 -pawn, and second, when  e4  is played White will threaten to win a piece by the fork  e5 . This is the first game where this plan was implemented and ever since then, given the right circumstances, it is one of White's best plans in the Carlsbad structure. }
